<file path="README.MD">
# Cyberhack: Breach Protocol Minigame 👾

A web-based recreation of the iconic "Breach Protocol" hacking minigame from Cyberpunk 2077. Built with **Rust**, **WebAssembly (Yew)**, and **Tailwind CSS v4**, designed to be highly performant and easily embeddable into React/Next.js applications.

![Cyberhack Preview](https://via.placeholder.com/800x450.png?text=Cyberhack+Minigame+Preview) _(Replace with an actual screenshot)_

## 🚀 Features

- **Authentic Mechanics:** Alternating row/column selection logic exactly like the original game.
- **WASM Performance:** Core logic written in Rust for lightning-fast execution and safety.
- **Neon UI:** Fully customized Cyberpunk aesthetic using Tailwind CSS v4, featuring CSS-based neon glow and flicker animations.
- **React Integration:** Native `postMessage` event bus to communicate game state (Win/Loss, Buffer data) to a parent React window.
- **Dark Mode First:** Tailored for dark themes with deeply customizable CSS variables (`oklch` color space).

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **[Rust](https://www.rust-lang.org/) & [Yew](https://yew.rs/):** Frontend framework for compiling Rust to WebAssembly.
- **[Tailwind CSS v4](https://tailwindcss.com/):** Utility-first CSS framework for rapid UI styling.
- **[Trunk](https://trunkrs.dev/):** Zero-config WASM web application bundler for Rust.

## 📦 Project Structure

```text
├── src/
│   └── main.rs          # Core game logic and Yew UI components
├── styles.css           # Source Tailwind directives and CSS variables
├── main.css             # Compiled Tailwind output
├── index.html           # Trunk entrypoint
├── Cargo.toml           # Rust dependencies
└── package.json         # Node scripts for CSS and React wrapper copying
```
